      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TERRA BELLA (3) produced a moderate run last time when seventh at this track over 520m behind Zipping Chebet (31.32) in a Grade 5. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from three attempts. Can make amends. SPIRALLING (8) ran a good time (29.55) when placing three back at Wentworth Park but has missed the frame since, last time out finishing sixth (26.10) at Temora. Expected to do much better this time. OXLEY CHARM (2) was strongly fancied latest and proved too good with a 0.8 lengths win at this track in a handy 30.22. Draws to advantage and has the ability and in winning form. Comes through a solid form race last start. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. ANOTHER IDEA (4) has top-three aspirations after placing at big odds last time.",
